summary: This is an automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating that a final travel voucher (ID 10892303-1(1)) has been approved. The voucher is for a trip related to the case 'U.S. v. Epstein' for a witness interview in Santa Monica, CA, from December 15-18, 2019.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Initiation
events.description: A trip was taken to Santa Monica, CA, for the purpose of conducting a witness interview related to the case U.S. v. Epstein.

events.title: Travel Voucher Approval
events.description: Final travel voucher 10892303-1(1) for the witness interview trip was approved by the DOJ's E2 system.

keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher approval email from the DOJ's E2 system dated December 30, 2019.
The voucher is for a trip taken from December 15-18, 2019, to Santa Monica, CA, for a witness interview related to the case 'U.S. v. Epstein'.
The voucher total expenses were $2,227.40, with an estimated trip cost of $2,440.58.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case in late 2019, after Epstein's death in August 2019.
The travel was for the specific purpose 'R20NYS13197 - U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interview (California)'.
